<h2><b>Who should attend?</b></h2>
<p>This event will bring together leaders, clinicians, allied healthcare staff and improvement practitioners involved in deploying Lean Thinking in teaching hospitals across the world.
    Delegates will have the opportunity to network with like-minded colleagues and learn what is and what is not working as we strive to improve patient care.
</p>
<h2><b>What are the themes of the Conference?</b></h2>
<p>The conference aims to <b><em>deepen our understanding of how lean thinking can deliver improvement for patients, staff and the organization</em></b>.
    The conference organizers are committed to building a program based on delegate contribution and will be attempting to provide answers to the following questions:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Where are our improvements focused and where are we achieving the most success?</li>
    <li>What are the examples of value stream redesign or active daily management system implementation where outcomes or lessons learned will deepen our knowledge of the approach?</li>
    <li>How are we developing our people to integrate problem solving and improvement into their work? What impact is this capability development having for our patients, staff and organization?</li>
    <li>Is Lean thinking helping us reduce costs? What progress have we made?</li>
</ul>
